Instructions on setting up mylar as a systemd service that will run on startup/via systemctl commands...

1 - copy the mylar.service to /lib/systemd/system/mylar.service
2 - edit the /lib/systemd/system/mylar.service file. (username, group, python path, Mylar.py path)

Make systemd aware of new services:
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable mylar

Start mylar
sudo systemctl start mylar

check to see if running
sudo systemctl status mylar
